<p>We are now going to introduce transliteration to assist in determining that you can actually read the Arabic.
In case one is not aware of what transliteration is, here is an example, basically it's nothing more than the English spelling 
of the Arabic. 
You will find that there are more than one way to transliterate a word/ sentence in the Arabic language.
Take for example, the word/phrase <span class="make-big">لۡحَمۡدُ لِلَّهِ</span> which transliterates into Al Hamdulillah.
You will also find that some will transliterate this word phrase as "AL Humdulillah", both are correct, but can cause some confussion to 
those who are just learning to read the Quran. At this point, you should've been able to 
read لۡحَمۡدُ لِلَّهِ

</p>
